cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to predict the popularity of online content using only its title. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to collect and preprocess the data, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The use of deep learning models and neural networks makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category. The paper also involves evaluation and optimization of the model, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with news articles and videos, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
